Infosys Ltd And International Business Machines Corp Secures $400 Million RBS Contract-Business Standard

Monday, 30 Sep 2013 08:37am EDT

Business Standard reported that Infosys Ltd and International Business Machines Corp (IBM) have won a EUR300 million (about INR2.535 billion) contract to develop the computer system for the UK-based bank Williams & Glyn's. The bank (Williams & Glyn's), which was dormant for about 30 years, is being revived by UK-based lender the Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc (RBSG). The bank is part of the RBS Group and is scheduled to launch operations by 2015.Â 

